&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audio Typist Administrator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 x full time (37.5) &amp; 1 x part time (25.5) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term Contract - for 1 year&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post will close once we have received a sufficient number of applications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an Audio Typist/ Administrator within Typing Services. The role is demanding and interesting and will require someone who is flexible and able to work under pressure and deal with a variety of tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be proficient in audio typing and will have good administrative skills. Excellent communication and customer service skills are essential for this post. Knowledge of medical terminology would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are enthusiastic, have good IT skills and enjoy working in a team then we would like to hear from you. In return we can offer you a supportive, fast moving and varied job, in an often busy environment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are a busy, friendly team, who would welcome the opportunity to work with a new member of staff willing to contribute to the on-going development of the services we provide.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: 15th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NAnne Goodsell, Team Leader Typing Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: annegoodsell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 020 8401 3000 x 4197&lt;/p&gt;
